JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 822
EP  - 835
VL  - 25
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study extends previous work concerning the attribution effect that knowledge of performance has on self-reported descriptions. In a laboratory experiment a two-dimensional involvement model was used: task involvement and group involvement. Results showed that the attribution effect previously demonstrated with complete participants holds for varying degrees of observers as well.
AB  - This study extends previous work concerning the attribution effect that knowledge of performance has on self-reported descriptions. In a laboratory experiment a two-dimensional involvement model was used: task involvement and group involvement. Results showed that the attribution effect previously demonstrated with complete participants holds for varying degrees of observers as well.
