TY  - JOUR
T1  - Group Size and Absenteeism Rates: A Longitudinal Analysis
AU  - Markham, Steven E.
AU  - Dansereau, Fred
AU  - Alutto, Joseph A.
Y1  - 1982/12/01
PY  - 1982
DA  - 1982/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256108
DO  - 10.5465/256108
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 921
EP  - 927
VL  - 25
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a study which examined whether absenteeism rates are related to the relative size of work groups as they change over time. The study has utilized data from the organizational records of a high technology manufacturing plant for the 1977-1978 period. The findings revealed a lack of evidence to support a between-group relationship between size of different groups and their absenteeism rates. The results have suggested that there can be a relationship between size and absenteeism when a within-group, overtime perspective is applied.
AB  - The article presents a study which examined whether absenteeism rates are related to the relative size of work groups as they change over time. The study has utilized data from the organizational records of a high technology manufacturing plant for the 1977-1978 period. The findings revealed a lack of evidence to support a between-group relationship between size of different groups and their absenteeism rates. The results have suggested that there can be a relationship between size and absenteeism when a within-group, overtime perspective is applied.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256108
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256108
Y2  - 2026/04/24
