JO  - AMJ
SP  - 707
EP  - 732
VL  - 25
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Measures of exit barriers and inducements to exit are constructed in a study of exits from nondeclining industries. Findings are contrasted with those from a study of exits within declining industries. The most significant factors influencing exit within mature, nondeclining industries were the presence of excess capacity and the apparent attractiveness of the industry.
AB  - Measures of exit barriers and inducements to exit are constructed in a study of exits from nondeclining industries. Findings are contrasted with those from a study of exits within declining industries. The most significant factors influencing exit within mature, nondeclining industries were the presence of excess capacity and the apparent attractiveness of the industry.
